MMR / Smmr
----------
The MMR decoder implements CCITT Group 4. Its run-length code tables
(src/mmr_tables.js) are the public ITU-T T.6 / T.4 standard codes.

The Smmr conformance test (tests/test_smmr.mjs) cross-checks the decoder against
an independent G4 decoder, tests/ccitt_oracle.mjs — the pure-JS CCITTFaxDecoder
vendored from pdf.js v3.11.174 (Copyright 2012 Mozilla Foundation), used under
the Apache License 2.0 (LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt). It is test-only (not part of
the shipped library); the only change from upstream is replacing a pdf.js util
import with local stubs.

IW44 wavelet
------------
The IW44 quantization steps and band structure follow the published IW44
wavelet design (L. Bottou et al.) and match DjvuNet's.

JPEG layers (BGjp / FGjp)
-------------------------
JPEG-layer decoding uses, as a fallback, a vendored pure-JS decoder at
src/jpeg.js, taken from jpeg-js (https://github.com/jpeg-js/jpeg-js). That file
is dual-provenance; both licenses apply and both are permissive:

  - The JPEG decoder core is Copyright (c) 2011 notmasteryet, licensed under the
    Apache License 2.0 (full text in LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt).
  - The jpeg-js packaging and modifications (including the decode() entry point
    used here) are Copyright (c) 2014 Eugene Ware, licensed under the
    BSD-3-Clause license (full text in LICENSES/BSD-3-Clause.txt).

The file is unmodified except for ES-module export wrappers appended at the end.
When the host provides a native JPEG codec (browser createImageBitmap), that is
used in preference to this decoder.

DjVuLibre
---------
The codecs here are an independent JavaScript implementation of the public DjVu
format, cross-referenced against the MIT-licensed DjvuNet (above). DjVuLibre
(the GPL reference implementation) is not included in, or distributed with, this
project, and no DjVuLibre source is present in this repository; it served as a
conformance test oracle — encoding the sample .djvu files used to validate
decoder output.
